  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nThe replica-healthcheck should not exit if it detects **any** errors. This original behaviour is causing issues with how components are started and isn't mindful of the different environments where the software may be running.\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nReplica-healthcheck should start and run until a SIGTERM signal is received from the operating system.\r\n\r\nNew metrics should be added.\r\n- `replica_health_connected` with a label of \"sequencer/upstream\" or \"replica\". The value `1` when network connections are successful, `0` when it's failing.\r\n- `replica_health_matching_state_root` metric where `1` means we're currently matching `0`, we're not matching ( and maybe `-1` not enough data)\r\n",
